<!--
  DRAFT TRANSLATIONS — Step 6.M-A.4 (2026-06-07)
  French (fr) UI translations, machine-drafted by Claude.
  ALL 135 keys in this file are DRAFT and require native speaker review
  before release.

  Critical strings (safety / medical disclaimer / user prompt) require
  professional translation, not just casual review:
    disclaimer_short
    companion_disclaimer
    mood_select_required
    settings_privacy_note
    companion_response_fallback

  Base tone: informal tu-form, wellbeing register, gender-neutral
  where possible (nouns for emotions to avoid m/f endings:
  Tristesse, Anxiété, Colère, Fatigue, Solitude, Surcharge, Calme,
  Espoir, Gratitude, Fierté, Paix, Motivation).

  Translation choices to flag for native reviewer:
   - "humeur" used for "mood" everywhere. Alternatives: "état
     d'esprit", "état émotionnel".
   - "pleine conscience" used for "mindfulness" (French native term).
     Alternative: keep English "mindfulness" as loanword.
   - "check-in" kept as English loanword. Alternatives:
     "enregistrement", "moment".
   - "Compagnon" used for "Companion" (masc form, French default for
     gender-neutral nouns).
   - Emotions translated as NOUNS to avoid m/f gender endings on
     adjectives (would force tu user into one gender). Spanish chose
     adjectives (masc default) and German chose adjectives in
     gender-neutral predicate form, but French adjectives always
     carry gender, so nouns are safer here.
   - "Bon retour" used for greeting — gender-neutral and warm.
     Alternative: "Te revoilà", "Heureux de te revoir" (gendered).
   - French typography spaces before ?, !, : are preserved as regular
     ASCII spaces. Native reviewer may want non-breaking spaces
     (U+00A0) for proper typography in a future revision.

  Apostrophe escaping: every ASCII apostrophe is escaped as \' as
  required by Android XML resources. The file contains ~25 such
  escapes (e.g. l\'humeur, d\'Elyria, n\'est, qu\'est-ce).

  See companion review document: Step_6MA4_French_Review.md
-->
